/*
 MySQL Connector/J

 This file represents the MySQL Connector library used in the project.

 MySQL Connector/J is a JDBC driver that allows Java applications to connect
 and interact with a MySQL database.

 It enables operations such as:
 - Connecting Java programs to MySQL
 - Executing SQL queries
 - Performing CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
 - Managing database transactions

 In this project, the connector is used by Database.java to establish
 a connection between the Java application and the MySQL database.

 The connection is created using JDBC with the following driver:

     com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver

 Example connection usage (in Database.java):

     Class.forName("com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver");
     Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(
         "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/supermarket",
         "root",
         ""
     );

 The connector JAR file (mysql-connector-j.jar) must be placed inside
 the 'lib' folder and added to the project libraries so the Java
 application can communicate with the MySQL server.

 Note:
 No executable Java code is written inside the connector file itself.
 It only provides the JDBC driver required for database connectivity.
*/
